r>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=291.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> TANKs in EQ</span><hr size=1> Most melee classes in Everquest do fit the definition of &quot;tank&quot; in other games.  All except rangers rogues and monks are better at taking damage than dealing it, and are outdamaged by most spell casters... Or at least thats how it was when I started playing.  Then came Kunark, then Velious, and now no only can a &quot;tank&quot; absorb far more damage than my wizard, they can also dish out more damage.  No, not just over the course of a fight, I mean in any given 10 second period.  But of course, we all know that and it is the central argument that wizards are unbalanced.<br>
<br>
Tanks are stepping on my spell caster toes in the damage department and I resent it.  <br>
<br>
My solution... if they aren't gonna give wizards more powerful nukes or mana regen, they should at least let us stomp back on the tanks' steel-plated feet.  If I can't have nukes, give me armor and weapons!  Yeah, let this little gnome wear cobalt armor and dual weild.  While yer at it, give me backstab too.  And if i get that, of course i'm gonna need feign death to dump off the aggro i cause.  <br>
<br>
All fear the wizarrior!!!<br>
<br>
Of course i'm just kidding about this, but its not too far off from what &quot;tanks&quot; are becomming if you think about it...<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxyntic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xyntic</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/01 2:45:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=291.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: TANKs in EQ</span><hr size=1> Just for a tidbit about warriors.  The word &quot;Myrmidon&quot; comes from the Greek language and means &quot;Ant&quot;.  An ant, alone by itself is nothing..but you put 1,000 ants together and they are a lethal force.  Looks like Verant took that to heart.  Put lots of warriors on a dragon and it's dead in seconds put lots of wizard on a dragon and you get lots of dead wizards.<br>
This was a good one a few days ago.  Killed Ragefire for cleric epic.  5 groups there to kill Naggy2, mostly tanks with only 1 wizard (me).  At 60% health, nuke was called, so I bravely stepped forward to do my part.  Lure of Lightning resisted, Lure of Frost hit for full, 2nd Lure of Frost partial.  Naggy2 then turns around, ignores ALL those tanks beating the crap out of it, and wanders over to smash my poor gnomish head into the ground.  I was the only casuality in the fight.  Woot!  GO ME!! <p><a href="http://www.elddarcaste.com/"target="web"><img src="http://www.elddarcaste.com/sigfile1.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubrexthegnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brex the gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/01 6:46:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=291.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> told ya</span><hr size=1> Hehe, see?  You shoulda been wearing yer cobalt and all would have been fine.  1 wizard alone isn't all that powerful, but many wizards together... well, uhh, they still aren't any more powerful, but ya gotta admit its cute (in a sad kinda way) to watch em try so hard.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Bah, annoying ants *reaches for his magnifying glass* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugherad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gherad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/28/01 4:32:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=291.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: told ya</span><hr size=1> Hehe, they actually called Nuke with just one wizard there?  They should have just let you use your best judgement.  Any wizard knows when it is safe to nuke - at least moreso than some silly melee type.<br>
<br>
Oh, and just use ice based lures on Ragefire.  I've never had one resisted. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/28/01 8:30:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=291.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> One minor exception to this theory...</span><hr size=1> Most of the examples given have been along the lines of the Uber Mob.  Yes, a group of 30 wizards isn't really going to have the same chance for success against a dragon as a similar sized group of tanks.<br>
<br>
However, the one place that our focused power is EXTREMELY clear is the ever popular AoE group.  Most of the time, when I have an AoE group in Sebi, and start pulling to &quot;zone in&quot; until we clear a path, the reaction from most others is...  &quot;HOLY !#$%@!  I wish I could do that.&quot;  But even in that situation, we still need that Cleric and Chanter.<br>
<br>
The only thing that I think is a LEGITIMATE reason for us to have our AC increased by items and armor, is the OBSCENELY STUPID idea of having to be at POINT BLANK RANGE for some of our spells to hit.  I mean, really.  We deal damage, we can't take it.  So why the hell would you create us that way, then PUNISH us.<br>
<br>
It is similar to the old French Monarchy situation where the upper class would bring children into a substandard living and educational environment and then punish them as adults for being poor and uneducated.  BRILLIANT!!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
